"Saku, do you want to be free?"\n<Yukine>\F[4]
"Yes. Saku wants to be with Yukine Onee-san."\n<Shuo>\F[4]\AA[FF]\FF[62]
"Yes. Saku wants to be with Yukine Onee-san."\n<Shuo>\F[4]\AA[FF]\FF[23]
"Saku... Are you also abandoning me? Even you..."\n<Sakari Tsuki>\FF[37]

"No! Saku is mine. You will live here for all
eternity. I'd rather die than hand you over to a
fox!"\n<Sakka Tsuki>\FF[37]
"As I thought, you protected him!"\n<Sakka Tsuki>\FF[32]

Sakugatsu sneers with a grin. The curse god knew
what I was trying to protect and deliberately
targeted Saku.

With a malevolent power gathered in his hand,
Sakugatsu thrusts a sharp hand blade filled with
murderous intent at me--

Despite clutching the amulet tightly, my wish did
not reach. A small hand pierced through my chest.

A scream echoes, and something hot spreads inside
my chest. My body trembles with the realization
that something that should not have broken has
shattered, and the sensation of life fading away--

As if to mock me for reaching out to the precious
girl, Sakuragatsu pulls out her arm.

And without waiting for the last word, the cursed
god crushes the tomato-like torn divine core in
her grasp.

In the darkening field of vision, I see
Sakuragatsu swallowing the shrunken heart. And as
I fall, Sakura's scream reaches my ears.
But there is nothing I can do.

As if mocking me for trying to defend myself with
a small knife, the tips of Sakurame Tsuki's
fingers undulated, making a slicing sound as they
passed by my neck.

Feeling something cold on my neck, a moment later,
bright red blood spurted from my throat.
"Onee-chan... no, no way... it's not true, right?"\n<Shuo>

You can hear Sakurame's voice. However, with my
throat slashed, I am unable to even respond.

I can clearly feel my life fading away. The blood
gushing out turns into particles of spiritual
energy and vanishes.

"To think you could deceive me, it's five hundred
years too early for you, vixen!"\n<Sakka Tsuki>

In the end, thinking of Sakurame until the last
moment, my head was severed by those small hands.

I unsheathed the small knife in my hand and swung
its rusty blade.

The blade, which should have been rusty, swept
away the approaching tentacles, and Sakuragatsu,
who lost everything beyond her wrist, screamed.

Upon closer inspection, the blade that was covered
in red rust had turned to shining silver, faintly
glowing. The light, like a lamp's flame, was a
gentle color as if protecting Saku.\AA[N]\FF[66]\F[4]
